Breakfast:
- "Veggie and cheese omlette"

  Ingredients:
  2 tablespoons butter, divided
  1 small onion, chopped
  1 green bell pepper, chopped
  ¾ teaspoon salt, divided
  4 large eggs
  2 tablespoons milk
  ⅛ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
  2 ounces shredded Swiss cheese

  Directions:
  1. In a bowl, beat 4 eggs with 2 tablespoons of milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and pepper.
  2. Melt another tablespoon of butter in the skillet, pour in the egg mixture, and let it set.
  3. Sprinkle 1/4 cup shredded cheese over the eggs, then spoon the vegetable mixture over half.
  4. Gently fold the omelet and cook until the cheese melts.
  5. Slide onto a plate, cut in half, and serve.

- "Protein Pancakes"

  Ingredients: 
  1 banana
  75g oats
  3 large eggs
  2 tbsp milk 
  1 tbsp baking powder
  2 tbsp protein powder 
  nut butter, maple syrup and berries or sliced banana to serve

  Directions:
  1. Blend together 1 banana, 1/2 cup oats, 2 eggs, 1/4 cup milk, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, and 1 scoop protein powder until smooth.
  2. Heat oil in a pan.
  3. Pour batter into rounds, cooking for 1-2 mins until bubbles form.
  4. Flip and cook for another minute.
  5. Serve with nut butter, maple syrup, and fruits.

Lunch: 
- "Chicken & tzatziki wraps"

Ingredients: 
1 cucumber, three-quarters deseeded and coarsely grated, the rest halved and sliced
250g Greek yogurt
500g chicken breast, thinly sliced
2tbsp olive oil
4 wholemeal wraps
4 large ripe tomatoes, thinly sliced

Directions:
1. Combine 1 grated cucumber and 1 cup yogurt for tzatziki, season.
2. Season chicken with salt and pepper, rub with 1 tbsp olive oil.
3. Cook chicken in 1 tbsp olive oil in a pan for 8-10 mins until golden brown.
4. Spread 2 tbsp tzatziki on each wrap.
5. Add chicken, tomatoes,sliced cucumber, and season with pepper
6. Fold sides over filling, roll up tightly, and serve.

- "Pesto spinach penne"

  Ingredients: 
  400g wholemeal penne
  5 tbsp vegetarian basil pesto
  500g baby spinach, roughly chopped
  220g cherry tomatoes, halved

  Directions:
  1. Cook the penne following pack instructions. 
  2. Meanwhile, heat 4 tbsp of the pesto in a non-stick pan over a medium-low heat. 
  3. Add the spinach and 2 tbsp water, then cover to wilt.
  4. Drain the pasta and toss with the spinach, the rest of the pesto and the tomatoes. 
  5. Serve half. Cool and chill the rest. Will keep chilled for three days. 
  6. Reheat with a splash of water.

- "Veggie Bacon Club Sandwich"

  Ingredients:

  3 slices thin sandwich bread, lightly toasted
  2 tablespoons mayonnaise
  2 slices cooked bacon, halved
  2 tomato slices
  ½ ounce thinly sliced Cheddar cheese
  ⅓ cup sliced cucumber
  ¼ cup shredded carrot
  2 large lettuce leaves

  Directions:
  1. Spread mayonnaise on one side of each toast slice. 
  2. Layer bacon and tomatoes on one slice. 
  3. Top with a second slice, then layer cheese, cucumber, carrot and lettuce. 
  4. Top with the third slice. 
  5. Slice the sandwich on the diagonal.

- "Chicken, Spinach & Feta Wrap"

  Ingredients:
  1/2 cup whole-milk plain strained (Greek-style) yogurt
  1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese
  2 tablespoons finely chopped oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes
  1 tablespoon dried oregano
  2 teaspoons grated lemon zest
  1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
  1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper
  1/4 teaspoon ground pepper
  2 cups shredded rotisserie chicken
  4 (10-inch) whole wheat tortillas
  4 cups packed fresh baby spinach

  Directions:
  1. Stir together 1 cup yogurt, 1/2 cup feta, sun-dried tomatoes, oregano, lemon zest, garlic powder, crushed red pepper, and pepper.
  2. Fold in chicken.
  3. Place 1 cup spinach and about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in the center of each tortilla.
  4. Fold bottom edge and side edges over the filling.
  5. Roll up burrito-style.
  6. Cut into halves before serving.

  Dinner:
- "Sheet-Pan Salmon with Crispy Quinoa:"

  Ingredients:
  4 (4.4-ounce) packages precooked microwaveable white and red quinoa (such as Minute) (about 2 3/4 cups)
  5 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided
  3 cups cherry tomatoes
  3 tablespoons drained nonpareil capers
  2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar
  1/4 teaspoon ground pepper
  4 (5-ounce) skin-on salmon fillets
  3/4 teaspoon salt, divided
  1/4 cup torn fresh basil leaves
  1/2 teaspoon refrigerated garlic paste
  1/2 teaspoon red-wine vinegar

  Directions:
  1. Preheat oven to 425°F and line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
  2. Spread quinoa on one sheet, drizzle with 2 tbsp oil, and toss to coat.
  3. On the other sheet, toss tomatoes with capers, balsamic vinegar, pepper, and 2 tbsp oil. 
  4. Arrange salmon fillets in the center, drizzle with 1 tbsp oil, and sprinkle with 1/4 tsp salt.
  5. Place quinoa on top rack and salmon on lower rack. Bake for about 15 minutes.
  6. Stir quinoa with a fork and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in remaining 1/2 tsp salt.
  7. Divide quinoa and salmon among 4 plates.
  8. Stir basil, garlic paste, and red-wine vinegar into tomato mixture. 
  9. Spoon over salmon before serving.






  Snacks:
- "Chicken Caesar Salad:"

  Ingredients:
  1 1/2 teaspoons Dijon mustard, divided
  1 teaspoon grated garlic, divided
  1/4 teaspoon ground pepper, divided
  8 ounces chicken tenders
  4 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided
  1/2 cup whole-milk plain strained (Greek-style) yogurt 
   5 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese, divided
  1 teaspoon lower-sodium Worcestershire sauce
  1/2 teaspoon anchovy paste
  1/4 teaspoon lemon juice
  4 cups chopped romaine lettuce hearts
  1/2 cup Caesar-seasoned croutons

Directions:
1. Combine 1 tsp mustard, 1/2 tsp garlic, and 1/8 tsp pepper in a bowl. Add chicken; coat evenly.
2. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. 
3. Cook chicken until golden brown and internal temperature reaches 165°F, 6-9 minutes. Let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
4. Whisk together yogurt, 3 tbsp Parmesan, Worcestershire sauce, anchovy paste, lemon juice, remaining 1/2 tsp mustard, 1/2 tsp garlic, and 1/8 tsp pepper until creamy.
5. Add lettuce to the dressing; toss to coat.
6. Divide dressed lettuce between 2 plates. Top with croutons and sliced chicken. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tbsp Parmesan.

